# A 12-factor-aligned agent intent: deterministic control flow, structured I/O, a human gate,
# bounded errors, a resumable lifecycle, and event triggers. Score it:
#   intent twelve-factor examples/TwelveFactorAgent.intent
mission TriageIncident
goal "triage an incoming incident and route it deterministically, pausing for a human on high-stakes actions"
why "on-call engineers need reliable, auditable triage, not an autonomous loop that can spin out"

requires monitoring signal
requires runbook access

scope
  include incident severity, service ownership, runbook steps
  exclude unrelated services, incidents older than 30 days

input
  severity: Severity
  service: ServiceId
  actor: UserId

output
  routing: RoutingDecision

guarantee every high-severity incident is acknowledged within the SLA
guarantee no destructive action runs without human approval

decision RouteIncident
  inputs
    severity
    ownerAvailable
  rule page
    when severity == "high" and ownerAvailable == true
    return PageOwner
  rule escalate
    when severity == "high" and ownerAvailable == false
    return EscalateToLead
  default
    return FileTicket

approval required from
  incident-commander

errors
  RunbookUnavailable
  DownstreamTimeout

on DownstreamTimeout
  compensate retry with backoff
  notify on-call channel

lifecycle IncidentLifecycle
  state Triaged
  state Routed
  state AwaitingApproval
  state Resolved
  transition route
    from Triaged
    to Routed
  transition await
    from Routed
    to AwaitingApproval
  transition resolve
    from AwaitingApproval
    to Resolved
  terminal Resolved

event IncidentRaised

demonstrates explains why high-severity incidents pause for human approval
requires_skill Incident Response, Distributed Systems
